what is business research  chroncom skip to main content what is business research by kimberleo companies use focus groups to sharpen their marketing strategy david woolleydigital visiongetty images related articles  business research  definition of business research  business research process  the steps in a business research process  business research  the nature  importance of business research  business research methods  types of business research methods business research is a field of practical study in which a company obtains data and analyzes it in order to better manage the company business research can include financial data consumer feedback product research and competitive analysis executives and managers who use business research methods are able to better understand their company the position it holds in the market and how to improve that position financial data financial data takes qualitative informationsuch as sales reports revenues and cost reportsto see what areas make money and what costs money by reviewing data managers can find the products staff and departments that are most efficient and determine areas of unnecessary costs consumer feedback understanding what the public says about the products and services a company provides is essential to making sure the company is meeting consumer needs customer feedback includes case studies focus groups customer surveys and questionnaires product research product research seeks to improve the product to meet the needs of consumers this may include technological advancements improved customer service or access to the product through a variety of distribution channels competitive analysis competitive analysis is when one company compares its products and services to those of another company this can be done to improve the product create a niche or determine a more attractive price point to lure customers industry data using research tools such as the information compiled by dun  bradstreet can help a company to understand how the industry as a whole is doing this can help executives make decisions based on economic factors affecting their industry that are not limited to their own products references  management library basic business research methods about the author in  kay miranda had her second screenplay purchased then started writing a weekly column in the messenger with work appearing in xquisite and valley scene magazine miranda earned a bachelor of arts in biopsychology from the university of colorado fortunate to play collegiate tennis miranda has extensive travel and coaching experience photo credits david woolleydigital visiongetty images suggest an article correction related searches more articles business research process  what is a business research process business research process necessary  why is the business research process necessary to assist managers business report  how to write a business report to an executive business research decisionmaking  steps involved in business research decisionmaking also viewed business research  what are the functions of business research consumer research process  the consumer research process scientific vs unscientific methods  scientific vs unscientific methods in business research research business  how to start a research business management decision  the importance of statistics in management decision making business proposal  steps to writing a business proposal development business strategies  the advantages of research  development business strategies res business management llc  ceo founder businessman  profile directorpedianet  list of ceos founders board members and company directors res business management llc check out list of companies and businesses related to res business management llc find out res business management llc address and contact details view other people related to res business management llc  coworkers colleagues companions etc address co a bennettconstellation brands inc  high po